  Item 3.03  Material Modification to Rights  
             of Security Holders.             
                                              
Upon issuance of the Series Z Preferred Stock 
(as defined in Item 5.03 below), the ability  
of The Goldman Sachs Group, Inc. (the         
“Registrant”) to declare or pay dividends on, 
or purchase, redeem or otherwise acquire,     
shares of its common stock will be subject to 
certain restrictions in the event that the    
Registrant fails to pay dividends on its      
Series Z Preferred Stock. These restrictions  
are set forth in the Certificate of           
Designations establishing the terms of the    
Series Z Preferred Stock, a copy of which is  
listed as Exhibit 3.1 to this Report on Form  
8-Kand is incorporated herein by reference.   
                                              
             Amendments to Articles of        
  Item 5.03  Incorporation or Bylaws; Change  
             in Fiscal Year.                  
                                              
On January 21, 2025, the Registrant filed a   
Certificate of Designations to its Restated   
Certificate of Incorporation with the         
Secretary of State of the State of Delaware   
setting forth the terms of its 6.850% Fixed-  
Rate Reset Non-CumulativePreferred Stock,     
Series Z, liquidation preference $25,000 per  
share (the “Series Z Preferred Stock”). A copy
of the Certificate of Designations relating to
the Series Z Preferred Stock is listed as     
Exhibit 3.1 to this Report on Form 8-Kand is  
incorporated herein by reference. Additional  
exhibits are filed herewith in connection with
the offering, issuance and sale of depositary 
shares representing interests in the          
Registrant’s Series Z Preferred Stock under   
the Registrant’s Registration Statement on    
Form S-3(File No. 333-269296).
